{
  "id": "22022421534",
  "title": "[ITD] Verify ITD during reset",
  "description": "<br />\n<h4>Flow *</h4>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\" id=\"isPasted\">During reset, while pCode periodic routines are not running, worst case temperature should be taken for the ITD correction.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">The value to use is MIN_TEMPERATURE for min and ITD_CUTOFF_TJ for max temperature.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">At reset phase 4 (after slowloops begin) pCode should track the temerature and compensate the voltage according to active state MoW.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><br /></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">1. Using itd.py calculate worst case ITD compensation.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">2. Triger reset and, using bootscript or an equivalent, halt before entering Phase 4.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">3. Verify that voltage value matches the calculated expectation.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">4. Resume boot and verify that new offset value is updated after CPL4 (Worst case no longer expected at this point).</p>\n<br />\n<h4>Configuration *</h4>\nNo specific configuration requirement identified.<br />\n<br />\n<h4>Pass/Fail criteria *</h4>\nFinal voltage for each domain equals the expected worst case value for the domain before reset phase 4.<p>After phase 4, ITD offset is no longer based on worst case temperature, so voltage value should decrease.</p><br />\n<br />\n<h4>Intent Verification Strategy *</h4>\nSimics.<br />\n<br />\n<h4>HW Requirements</h4>\nN/A<br />\n<br />\n<h4>SW Requirements</h4>\nBootscript, Pcode, Acode, Patch23.<br />\n<br />\n<h4>Coverage</h4>\nN/A<br />\n<br />\n<h4>Component Interactions</h4>\nN/A<br />\n<br />",
  "parent_id": "16031170075",
  "status": "open"
}